# Lazyweb MCP (design research / UI references)
# 1) Request a free install token (use lazyweb.com if www returns 502):
#    curl -sSL -X POST https://lazyweb.com/api/mcp/install-token \
#      -H "content-type: application/json" -d '{}'
# 2) Set LAZYWEB_MCP_TOKEN for Cursor (pick one):
#    - Add to your shell profile and fully quit/reopen Cursor, or
#    - Cursor Settings → search "env" / MCP environment if your build supports it, or
#    - Add the same line to a gitignored file that your tooling loads (e.g. .env.local if you load it into the environment Cursor inherits).
# 3) Reload Cursor (Developer: Reload Window) so .cursor/mcp.json picks up the variable.
#
LAZYWEB_MCP_TOKEN=
